external_knowledge:
- "owners" refers to users who have created projects in the database;
- "more than one project" means the owner has at least two projects;
- "share at least one project" means there is at least one project that two different owners both own.

- "blooming in the garden of changes" refers to the occurrence or presence of different types of modifications in the database;
- `mod_type` includes various types such as 'added', 'deleted', etc.;
- `modification_count` is the count of each `mod_type` in the `modifications` table.

- A project can be thought of as a tree with an initial modification as the root and other modifications as branches;
- The cumulative number of lines modified represents the growth of the tree from the root to the branches;
- The level in the hierarchy represents the depth of the branches from the root.

- A "pull request" is a proposal to merge changes from one branch into another in a version-controlled repository;
- "Project activity" can be measured by the number of pull requests, indicating the level of development and collaboration;
- "Top 10" refers to the highest-ranking projects based on the specified metric.
